    "text": "Your number is fine, and the comparison to online figures is the part to drop. Today's HRV is 57 ms against your own 30-day average of 61.6 ms with a standard deviation of about 4.7, so you're within your normal band, and your 7-day average of 60 ms says the trend is steady. HRV values are not comparable across people or methods: your feed computes it as SDNN from mixed sources, while many published numbers use different math and different measurement windows, so the absolute values simply live on different scales. The only comparison that means anything is you versus your own baseline. Note your setup doesn't produce a recovery score, so HRV against baseline is your main readiness signal; keep watching direction, not the raw number.",
